xist critics Raymond Williams and Fredric Jameson, brings Chicano literature into the arena of contemporary literary theory. By focusing on an important but little-studied poetic tradition, his book challenges our ideas of the American canon and extends the reach of Hispanists and folklorists as well.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aAmerican poetryxMexican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aAmerican poetryxMexican influences. 0aBallads, SpanishxAppreciationxMexicoxUnited States. 0aBallads, SpanishxAppreciationzMexicozUnited States. 0aBallads, SpanishzMexicoxAppreciationzUnited States. 0aMexican Americans in literature. 0aMexican AmericansxIntellectual life. 0aSocial problems in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press eBook Package Archivez978311063534840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520911871423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520911871.jpg  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press eBook Package Archive  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles